text: Carob moths are certain species of small snout moths (family Pyralidae). They are named for their caterpillars' habit of becoming a pest on stored fruits of carob (Ceratonia siliqua). The term can refer to: * Ectomyelois ceratoniae (locust bean moth) * Cadra calidella (dried fruit moth) Category:Animal common name disambiguation pages
title: Carob moth
